description.p:
To achieve the aforementioned objects, the invention is a center bearing diaphragm which provides radial and axial freedom of motion to the drive shaft; comprises a diaphragm which is made of an elastic material and the inner and outer surfaces of which are supported by a bearing cup and a mounting plate, respectively, and a bearing which is centered by said bearing cup, characterized in further comprising
a cord fabric comprising layers and lattice structures at a desired number in said diaphragm;
support surfaces comprising cascade surfaces gripping said bearing cup and mounting plate;
an outer knuckle having a protrusion in the inner surface thereof providing a high resistance and surfaces gripping said bearing cup from the large surface.
